<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-24T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2981</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Saloniki</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KJE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kehl</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Saloniki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-24T17:00:00+02:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 25, 12.30 p.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your October 21, 5 p. m. Shall act in accordance with my telegram of
                            October 13, 1 p. m. Minister of Finance Provisional authorities has
                            written that he considered Consulate’s relations informal and
                            unofficial, and expressed intention of asking Government of United
                            States for official recognition in near future.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consul</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>